-- ComplexNumber/trigonometry.math
--
-- Cosine and sine, defined FROM the complex exponential (not as
-- standalone power series):
--
--   cosine(x) := Re(exp(i·x)),   sine(x) := Im(exp(i·x)).
--
-- Euler's formula exp(i·x) = cos(x) + i·sin(x) is then literally the
-- coordinate reconstruction of exp(i·x). The power-series
-- characterisations become theorems later (realPart_partialSum + the
-- i-power 4-cycle); sin² + cos² = 1 and the addition formulas wait on
-- the ℂ functional equation and conjugation.

